lity has been decreasing as traditionally poor countries’ economies have caught up with the West. The report shows, however, that inequality has been steadily deepening within almost every nation, though national trajectories vary, suggesting the importance of institutional and policy frameworks in shaping inequality. The World Inequality Report: 2018 will be a key document for anyone concerned about one of the most imperative and contentious subjects in contemporary politics and economics.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aEconomic historyy21st century. 0aEconomic history-21st century. 0aEqualityxEconomic aspectsvCross-cultural studies. 0aEquality-Economic aspects-Cross-cultural studies. 0aIncome distributionvCross-cultural studies. 0aIncome distribution-Cross-cultural studies. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Economic Conditions.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHarvard University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311060662140uhttps://doi.org/10.4159/978067498476940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780674984769423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780674984769.jpg  a978-3-11-060662-1  Harvard University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles